<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - OIL PAN, VIBRATION DAMPER, OIL
        PUMP, WATER PUMP, AND FRONT COVER - Inspection - Oil Pump
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="2">
        <title>Oil Pump</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the gerotors and housing for nicks, burrs or scoring. Replace any damaged
                components.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>When placing the inner and outer gerotors into the oil pump housing, make sure the word "damper"
                    is facing the oil pump housing. Failure to do so will result in engine damage.
                </para>
            </caution>
            <note>
                <para>The inner and outer gerotors are a matched set. They cannot be replaced separately.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the inner and outer gerotors in the oil pump housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200518" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1443.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Inspecting Gerotors For Wear</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Outer Gerotor</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Pump Housing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Feeler Gauge</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To check for wear, use a feeler gauge to measure the radial clearance between the outer
                gerotor and the pump housing.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200519" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1442.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Checking the Oil Pump End Clearance</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil Pump Housing</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Gerotors</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Feeler Gauge</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Straightedge</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the oil pump end clearance as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">With the O-ring removed and the gerotors in place in the oil pump housing, place a
                    straightedge across the housing.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Insert a feeler gauge under the straightedge at the inner and outer gerotors and compare
                    the end clearance with the specification.
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the measurements are not within the specifications, replace the components as required.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
